catProfiles.profile: {"name":"JUANCHITO","age":16,"distance":33,"text":"York Chocolate cats are known to be true lap cats with a sweet temperament. They love to be cuddled and petted. Their curious nature makes them follow you all the time and participate in almost everything you do, even if it's related to water: unlike many other cats, York Chocolates love it.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/LzVDEMYIv.jpg"}

{"name":"ESMERALDA","age":7,"distance":42,"text":"They are known for their size and luxurious long coat Maine Coons are considered a gentle giant. The good-natured and affable Maine Coon adapts well to many lifestyles and personalities. She likes being with people and has the habit of following them around, but isn’t needy. Most Maine Coons love water and they can be quite good swimmers.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/OOD3VXAQn.jpg"}

{"name":"EVITA","age":7,"distance":38,"text":"The Norwegian Forest Cat is a sweet, loving cat. She appreciates praise and loves to interact with her parent. She makes a loving companion and bonds with her parents once she accepts them for her own. She is still a hunter at heart. She loves to chase toys as if they are real. She is territorial and patrols several times each day to make certain that all is fine.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/L_H7aef7m.jpg"}

{"name":"MADELINE","age":18,"distance":48,"text":"Savannah is the feline version of a dog. Actively seeking social interaction, they are given to pouting if left out. Remaining kitten-like through life. Profoundly loyal to immediate family members whilst questioning the presence of strangers. Making excellent companions that are loyal, intelligent and eager to be involved.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/qf6MhNS8z.jpg"}

{"name":"CHUIYA","age":7,"distance":10,"text":"The Burmilla is a fairly placid cat. She tends to be an easy cat to get along with, requiring minimal care. The Burmilla is affectionate and sweet and makes a good companion, the Burmilla is an ideal companion to while away a lonely evening. Loyal, devoted, and affectionate, this cat will stay by its owner, always keeping them company.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/r530zDuJU.jpg"}

{"name":"RHIJHIK","age":4,"distance":27,"text":"The Abyssinian is easy to care for, and a joy to have in your home. They’re affectionate cats and love both people and other animals.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/TGuAku7fM.jpg"}

{"name":"PAGET","age":13,"distance":25,"text":"The Korat is a natural breed, and one of the oldest stable cat breeds. They are highly intelligent and confident cats that can be fearless, although they are startled by loud sounds and sudden movements. Korats form strong bonds with their people and like to cuddle and stay nearby.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/xPuWATvp9.jpg"}

{"name":"CHEMITA","age":15,"distance":20,"text":"The Exotic Shorthair is a gentle friendly cat that has the same personality as the Persian. They love having fun, don’t mind the company of other cats and dogs, also love to curl up for a sleep in a safe place. Exotics love their own people, but around strangers they are cautious at first. Given time, they usually warm up to visitors.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/u3V0SSE-F.jpg"}

{"name":"AZRAEL","age":15,"distance":10,"text":"The Nebelung may have a reserved nature, but she loves to play (being especially fond of retrieving) and enjoys jumping or climbing to high places where she can study people and situations at her leisure before making up her mind about whether she wants to get involved.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/FotU1pOJT.jpg"}

{"name":"SARI","age":10,"distance":45,"text":"The Toyger has a sweet, calm personality and is generally friendly. He's outgoing enough to walk on a leash, energetic enough to play fetch and other interactive games, and confident enough to get along with other cats and friendly dogs.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/_rnhm7vpT.jpg"}

{"age":6,"distance":35,"text":"Loving, loyal, social and inquisitive, the Cyprus cat forms strong ties with their families and love nothing more than to be involved in everything that goes on in their surroundings. They are not overly active by nature which makes them the perfect companion for people who would like to share their homes with a laid-back relaxed feline companion. ","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/cruhNBsv1.jpg","name":"CROQUE"}

{"age":4,"distance":33,"text":"This is a smart and intelligent cat which bonds well with humans. With its affectionate and playful personality the Angora is a top choice for families. The Angora gets along great with other pets in the home, but it will make clear who is in charge, and who the house belongs to","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/GIpj4xxPA.jpg","name":"ELAINE"}

{"age":14,"distance":40,"text":"The Munchkin is an outgoing cat who enjoys being handled. She has lots of energy and is faster and more agile than she looks. The shortness of their legs does not seem to interfere with their running and leaping abilities.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/vXiNSY60T.jpg","name":"ROXANNE"}

{"age":12,"distance":45,"text":"The favourite perch of the Devon Rex is right at head level, on the shoulder of her favorite person. She takes a lively interest in everything that is going on and refuses to be left out of any activity. Count on her to stay as close to you as possible, occasionally communicating his opinions in a quiet voice. She loves people and welcomes the attentions of friends and family alike.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/lJHXU7DlQ.jpg","name":"BOB"}

{"age":4,"distance":46,"text":"The Abyssinian is easy to care for, and a joy to have in your home. They’re affectionate cats and love both people and other animals.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/gCEFbK7in.jpg","name":"MR BOO BOO"}

{"age":10,"distance":18,"text":"The Siberians dog like temperament and affection makes the ideal lap cat and will live quite happily indoors. Very agile and powerful, the Siberian cat can easily leap and reach high places, including the tops of refrigerators and even doors. ","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/--ovPy5Lb.jpg","name":"MEREDITH"}

{"age":10,"distance":1,"text":"Orientals are passionate about the people in their lives. They become extremely attached to their humans, so be prepared for a lifetime commitment. When you are not available to entertain her, an Oriental will divert herself by jumping on top of the refrigerator, opening drawers, seeking out new hideaways.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/NTsRW30uC.jpg","name":"BUGS"}

{"age":16,"distance":1,"text":"The British Longhair is a very laid-back relaxed cat, often perceived to be very independent although they will enjoy the company of an equally relaxed and likeminded cat. They are an affectionate breed, but very much on their own terms and tend to prefer to choose to come and sit with their owners rather than being picked up.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/i-j1kCi3b.jpg","name":"BAGEL"}

{"age":7,"distance":17,"text":"The Somali lives life to the fullest. He climbs higher, jumps farther, plays harder. Nothing escapes the notice of this highly intelligent and inquisitive cat. Somalis love the company of humans and other animals.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/ayEJiATFy.jpg","name":"MS MINNIE"}

{"age":4,"distance":27,"text":"Arabian Mau cats are social and energetic. Due to their energy levels, these cats do best in homes where their owners will be able to provide them with plenty of playtime, attention and interaction from their owners. These kitties are friendly, intelligent, and adaptable, and will even get along well with other pets and children.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/zlpgGWqN7.jpg","name":"PENELOPE"}

{"age":7,"distance":34,"text":"The Ragamuffin is calm, even tempered and gets along well with all family members. Changes in routine generally do not upset her. She is an ideal companion for those in apartments, and with children due to her patient nature.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/GcZbVDVi8.jpg","name":"MARSHMALLOW"}

{"age":17,"distance":31,"text":"The Bambino is a breed of cat that was created as a cross between the Sphynx and the Munchkin breeds. The Bambino cat has short legs, large upright ears, and is usually hairless. They love to be handled and cuddled up on the laps of their family members.","img":"https://cdn2.thecatapi.com/images/Oaoo1ky3A.jpg","name":"PEAK"}
